nature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"4e72aa3e13fa7310b8c052e7b1833da6ad7a3610409f799c260317961201e7e7","event_uuid":"41ed8037-607d-4077-b6c1-53d019c82d13","position":{"commit_sha":"25e9459f2e1acfd54214e794a3b9a1e289e18933","position":"1784822388871991001-41ed8037-607d-4077-b6c1-53d019c82d13"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":null,"claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":null,"comments":[],"created_at":1784517456619430001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[],"description":"## Description\nFoundation seam for the code_health lens: a language-agnostic analyzer protocol + a per-language *selection* helper the metric readers call instead of scanning hardcoded paths. No tool shell-outs yet — ship the protocol, the selector, and a null/default analyzer so the contract is testable in isolation (additive; changes no existing behavior).\n\n## Review-driven corrections\n- REUSE the existing `rebar.metrics.registry.Unavailable(reason, accruing_since)` sentinel (the SAME shape the CLI renders as `{reason, accruing_since}`) — do NOT invent a single-arg `Unavailable(\"...\")`; the fallback helper returns `Unavailable(reason=\"no analyzer configured for <lang>\", accruing_since=<ts>)`.\n- Do NOT name the new concept \"registry\"/\"REGISTRY\" (collides with `metrics/registry.py` + module-level `REGISTRY`). Use e.g. `ANALYZERS` map + `resolve_analyzer(lang)`.\n- New adapters (later tickets) live in a NEW `src/rebar/metrics/analyzers/` package, NOT `adapters/` (which is quarantined: imported only by harvest/backfill scripts, never by core/registry).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] `Analyzer` protocol + `AnalyzerResult` (fields loc/complexity/duplication, each optional=None when unsupported).\n- [ ] `resolve_analyzer(lang)` returns None when none configured; fallback helper returns the reused `Unavailable(reason, accruing_since)` — NEVER scans a path, fabricates zeros, or leaks an exception string.\n- [ ] Pure stdlib; import registers nothing into `REGISTRY` as a side effect (opt-in wiring lands in 0734).\n\n## Verification\n- [ ] Unit: miss -> Unavailable(reason, accruing_since); support -> AnalyzerResult passthrough. `make lint` + `pytest tests/unit/metrics`.\n\n## Dependencies: None (keystone; blocks 9597, e7a0, 18f9, 21fb, 3ba0, 0734)\n## Files likely touched: src/rebar/metrics/analyzer.py (new), tests/unit/metrics/test_analyzer.py (new)\n## Estimated scope: M","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/metrics/analyzer.py","reason":"new: analyzer protocol + registry + Unavailable fallback helper"},{"path":"tests/unit/metrics/test_analyzer.py","reason":"new: lookup-miss->Unavailable, passthrough on support"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","839b-f6d2-7e1a-4051"]],"parent_id":"839b-f6d2-7e1a-4051","parent_status_uuid":"da392196-53b6-4520-b4d1-8613e7b6b655","plan_review_phase":"execution","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["metrics","code-health"],"ticket_id":"3b30-2168-ba16-41fc","ticket_type":"story","title":"Define the code-health analyzer interface + hard Unavailable fallback contract","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["76bc5f65-f87f-434a-aa21-c1660453885e","8fdc4596-c27c-4dfa-b763-98960cd7b734","ba52c2a9-e4bc-45e2-b06c-2fa218229b7f","0b79d0d2-0027-492f-aa78-2e2f0c2af0cc","